<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-07-17T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-07-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="10" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G 1A/147: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-17T16:00:00-05:00">July 17, 1933—4
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>65. Legation’s 62, July 13, 8 p.m. Olaya<note n="12" xml:id="d10fn12">Enrique Olaya-Herrera, President of Colombia.</note> says
                                Minister for Foreign Affairs misunderstood his idea. What he hopes
                                for is presentation by the United States at Seventh Pan-American
                                Conference of resolution or other document embodying all proposals
                                in President Roosevelt’s disarmament message.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>